  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Esther Sturge asks Mrs. Maria Weston Chapman: &quot;Did you see the reply of the Austrian minister to the address from America on the Hungarian cause?&quot; It &quot;reflects so justly on the disgrace of the Americans; asks how they can, holding 3,000,000 of Bondsmen (Slaves) affect to legislate for Austria &amp; meddle with her institutions etc.&quot; The fugitive slave Henson was cleared and &quot;found truly honest.&quot; Esther Sturge deplores that private sentiments should mar the unity of anti-slavery efforts. Sturge asks if Maria W. Chapman&apos;s brother is fully recovered, &quot;and how is thy dear Son?&quot; Esther Sturge asks: &quot;Have you met with my dear sister.&quot;</subfield>
